sentences: Huh Chan-mi (Korean: 허찬미; born April 6, 1992), is a South Korean singer.

Huh first made her debut as a member of a South Korean co-ed group Coed School in 2010 and following the co-ed group were split, Huh later became the girl unit F-ve Dolls in 2011 until her departure from the group in February 2012.
